---
source: crates/aikido-core/tests/sentaku_test.rs
expression: list
---
- "double-satisfaction                      [Critical] Detects spend handlers that iterate outputs without referencing their own OutputReference"
- "missing-redeemer-validation              [High] Detects catch-all redeemer patterns that trivially return True"
- "missing-validity-range                   [Medium] Detects handlers with time-like datum fields that never check validity_range"
- "missing-signature-check                  [High] Detects handlers with authority-like datum fields that never check extra_signatories"
- "unsafe-datum-deconstruction              [High] Detects spend handlers with Option<T> datum that never use `expect Some(x) = datum`"
- "unbounded-list-iteration                 [Medium] Detects direct iteration over raw transaction list fields (outputs, inputs, etc.)"
- "hardcoded-addresses                      [Medium] Detects ByteArray literals with lengths matching Cardano key hashes or addresses"
- "missing-minting-policy-check             [Critical] Detects mint handlers that don't validate which token names are being minted"
- "missing-utxo-authentication              [Critical] Detects handlers that use reference inputs without authenticating them"
- "unrestricted-minting                     [Critical] Detects minting policies with no authorization check"
- "unused-validator-parameter               [Medium] Detects validator parameters that are never referenced in any handler"
- "fail-only-redeemer-branch                [Low] Detects redeemer when/match branches that always fail"
- "missing-datum-in-script-output           [High] Detects handlers that produce outputs without verifying datum attachment"
- "arbitrary-datum-in-output                [High] Detects handlers that produce outputs with datum but don't validate datum correctness"
- "insufficient-staking-control             [Medium] Detects handlers that produce outputs without constraining the staking credential"
- "unbounded-datum-size                     [Medium] Detects datum types with unbounded fields (List, ByteArray) that could exceed processing limits"
- "division-by-zero-risk                    [High] Detects division/modulo operations where the denominator could be attacker-controlled"
- "non-exhaustive-redeemer                  [Medium] Detects redeemer pattern matches that may not cover all constructors"
- "unsafe-list-head                         [Medium] Detects use of list.head() or list.at() which crash on empty lists"
- "token-name-not-validated                 [High] Detects minting policies that check authorization but don't validate token names"
- "value-not-preserved                      [High] Detects spend handlers that don't verify output value covers input value"
- "unbounded-value-size                     [Medium] Detects outputs that don't constrain the number of native assets in the Value"
- "oracle-freshness-not-checked             [Medium] Detects use of oracle data without verifying recency (timestamp/slot check)"
- "missing-min-ada-check                    [Info] Detects script outputs without ensuring minimum ADA requirement"
- "dead-code-path                           [Low] Detects code paths that can never be reached"
- "redundant-check                          [Low] Detects redeemer branches with trivially true conditions"
- "shadowed-variable                        [Info] Detects handler parameters shadowed by when/match pattern bindings"
- "magic-numbers                            [Info] Detects unexplained numeric literals in validator logic"
- "excessive-validator-params               [Info] Detects validators with too many parameters"
- "unused-import                            [Info] Detects validators with no function calls to imported modules"
- "unsafe-partial-pattern                   [Medium] Detects expect patterns on non-Option types that may fail at runtime"
- "unconstrained-recursion                  [Medium] Detects handlers calling themselves without clear termination"
- "empty-handler-body                       [Medium] Detects handlers with no meaningful logic"
- "utxo-contention-risk                     [Medium] Detects validators with single global UTXO contention patterns"
- "cheap-spam-vulnerability                 [Medium] Detects validators vulnerable to cheap UTXO spam attacks"
- "unsafe-match-comparison                  [High] Detects unsafe use of match(..., >=) for Cardano Value comparison"
- "integer-underflow-risk                   [Medium] Detects integer subtraction that may produce negative values without a guard"
- "quantity-of-double-counting              [High] Detects multiple quantity_of calls on the same Value that may allow asset overlap exploitation"
- "output-address-not-validated             [Critical] Detects handlers that produce outputs without verifying the destination address"
- "missing-datum-field-validation           [Medium] Detects spend handlers that accept datum with financial fields but never validate them"
- "reference-script-injection               [Low] Detects outputs that don't constrain reference_script, allowing script injection"
- "missing-token-burn                       [Medium] Detects minting policies with no burn (negative quantity) handling"
- "state-transition-integrity               [High] Detects spend handlers with multiple redeemer actions but no output datum verification"
- "missing-state-update                     [Medium] Detects spend handlers that produce continuing outputs without datum state updates"
- "withdraw-zero-trick                      [High] Detects handlers using withdrawal-based auth without verifying withdrawal amounts"
- "other-token-minting                      [High] Detects minting policies that don't restrict other policies from minting in the same tx"
- "rounding-error-risk                      [Medium] Detects handlers with integer division and multiplication that risk precision loss"
- "missing-input-credential-check           [Medium] Detects handlers that search inputs by token/value without verifying credential type"
- "unsafe-redeemer-arithmetic               [High] Detects division or multiplication with attacker-controlled redeemer values"
- "duplicate-asset-name-risk                [Medium] Detects minting policies that don't verify token name uniqueness"
- "value-preservation-gap                   [High] Detects spend handlers that check lovelace but not native asset preservation"
- "fee-calculation-unchecked                [Medium] Detects fee/deduction calculations using attacker-controlled redeemer values"
- "uncoordinated-multi-validator            [High] Detects multi-handler validators where spend doesn't verify minting"
- "datum-tampering-risk                     [Medium] Detects continuing outputs where only some datum fields are validated"
- "missing-burn-verification                [High] Detects value reduction in spend handlers without verifying token burns"
- "oracle-manipulation-risk                 [High] Detects reference input usage without payment credential verification"
- "missing-protocol-token                   [Medium] Detects continuing outputs without state token verification"
- "unbounded-protocol-operations            [Medium] Detects handlers iterating both inputs and outputs (O(n*m) risk)"
- "unused-library-module                    [Info] Detects library modules not used by any validator"
- "value-comparison-semantics               [High] Detects unsafe multi-asset Value comparison patterns"
- "output-count-validation                  [Medium] Detects spend handlers producing script outputs without checking output count"
- "tautological-comparison                  [Critical] Detects comparisons where a value is compared to itself (always true)"
- "path-sensitive-guard-check               [High] Detects variables guarded on some paths but not others"
- "precise-taint-to-sink                    [High] Detects unsanitized attacker-controlled data reaching sensitive operations"
- "dead-branch-detection                    [Info] Identifies unreachable or always-failing branches"
- "cross-validator-gap                      [High] Detects potential gaps in delegated validation"
- "uncoordinated-state-transfer             [Medium] Detects uncoordinated state transfers between validators"
- "incomplete-burn-flow                     [High] Detects destructive operations missing token burns across validators"
- "multi-asset-comparison-bypass            [High] Detects Value comparison that can be bypassed with extra assets"
- "incomplete-value-extraction              [Medium] Detects partial Value checks via quantity_of that miss other assets"
- "identity-token-forgery                   [High] Detects tokens used for identity without minting policy verification"
- "withdraw-amount-check                    [Medium] Detects withdrawal auth that only checks existence, not amount"
- "state-machine-violation                  [High] Detects state machine issues in redeemer handling"
- "invariant-violation                      [High] Detects potential value conservation violations"
- "datum-field-bounds                       [Medium] Detects datum fields without bounds validation"
